  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For example, think about the rule instance</html:p><html:p><fr:resource hash="859f4110b517626de6dba626bb89e1d1"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/lectures/859f4110b517626de6dba626bb89e1d1.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {ebproof}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
\begin {prooftree}
\hypo {p \;/\; q}
\infer 1[]{p \land  q \;/\; r}
\end {prooftree}
]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:p><html:p>Which of the following logics obeys this rule instance?
<html:ol><html:li>the logic that contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \;/\; A]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> has exactly one member</html:li>
<html:li>the logic that contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \;/\; A]]></fr:tex> iff all members of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> are atomic</html:li>
<html:li>the logic that contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \;/\; A]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> has three or more members</html:li></html:ol></html:p>

	
	
	
	<fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/lectures/ellieripley/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/ellieripley/" display-uri="ellieripley" type="local">Ellie Ripley</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>7</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Solution</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:ol><html:li>This logic does obey the rule instance, since the conclusion-argument is valid in the logic.</html:li>
<html:li>This logic does not obey the rule instance, since the premise-argument is valid in the logic but the conclusion-argument is not.</html:li>
<html:li>This logic does obey the rule instance, since there is a premise-argument that is not valid in the logic.</html:li></html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter>
