\hypo {p \;/\; q}
\infer 1[]{p \land  q \;/\; r}
\end {prooftree}
]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:p><html:p>Which of the following logics obeys this rule instance?
<html:ol><html:li>the logic that contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \;/\; A]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> has exactly one member</html:li>
<html:li>the logic that contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \;/\; A]]></fr:tex> iff all members of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> are atomic</html:li>
