	<fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/lectures/ellieripley/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/ellieripley/" display-uri="ellieripley" type="local">Ellie Ripley</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>7</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Solution</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:ol><html:li>This logic does obey the rule instance, since the conclusion-argument is valid in the logic.</html:li>
<html:li>This logic does not obey the rule instance, since the premise-argument is valid in the logic but the conclusion-argument is not.</html:li>
<html:li>This logic does obey the rule instance, since there is a premise-argument that is not valid in the logic.</html:li></html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/lectures/ellieripley/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/ellieripley/" display-uri="ellieripley" type="local">Ellie Ripley</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>4</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>7</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://negation.rocks/lectures/006A/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>006A</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/lectures/006A/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Rule, obeying a rule">Rule, obeying a rule</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:strong>rule</html:strong> is a set of rule instances.
A logic <html:strong>obeys</html:strong> a rule iff it obeys every member of the rule.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>A rule collects up a bunch of rule instances into a single package.
You can think of a rule as placing a whole lot of conditions on a logic at once: one for each rule instance in it.
To obey a rule, a logic has to obey all its instances.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
